 Bonginkosi Makua (20) allegedly hacked his mother, Phindile Shongwe (40), to death with a panga.
The gruesome attack took place on Women’s Day in Emtonjeni near Machadodorp. A man reportedly hit her several times over the head and neck, resulting in her bleeding to death.
Police found the panga underneath a bed in Ms Shongwe’s home. According to information, the deceased was an Emakhazeni Local Municipality employee. The Belfast Magistrate’s Court was filled with ANC members on Monday, when Mr Makua made his first court appearance.    Watch: Armed robbers open fire on unsuspecting civilians Man shot in Midwater heist succumbs to wounds Municipal security providers ‘not black enough’  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za